Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.61,0:01:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{勝利と敗北の間}—Episode 017—\NVictory is not everything
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.77,0:01:49.67,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{え？}Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.67,0:01:54.12,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{バレー部XXX体育館建設をソ連との試合にかかってるんですって？}You wagered the construction of the new gym on winning with the Soviet Union?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.12,0:01:58.04,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{と言うことは、ソ連に勝たなければ、体育館をXXXてことね？}So if we don't win with the Soviet Union, there's no gym?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.04,0:01:58.86,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{え。そうなの。}Yep, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.86,0:02:03.26,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{だからこうなったらあたしたち何が何でもソ連に勝たなければ成らないのよ。}This is why we have to win with the Soviet Union no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.26,0:02:04.94,Default,(unison),0,0,0,,{え？}Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.94,0:02:06.06,Default,Fukuda,0,0,0,,{何が何でも。}No matter what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.20,0:02:08.17,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{そうよ。ね？}Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.17,0:02:09.47,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{勝ちましょう。}Let's win.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.27,0:02:13.93,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{皆、どうしたの？黙ってしまって。}Why are you so quiet all of the sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.93,0:02:16.50,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{「よし、やろう」って言ってくれないの？}Where's the usual "Yeah! Let's do this!"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.50,0:02:21.72,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{そうよ。本郷先生からソ連との試合聞いた時、皆あんなに張り切ってなのに。}Yeah. You all were so enthusiastic in front of professor Hongou earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.56,0:02:28.26,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{それとも、それとも皆ソ連に勝つ自身をなくしてしまったの？}Or do you want to say you lost your confidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.26,0:02:29.74,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{ね、カッコ。}Hey, Kakko.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.74,0:02:30.76,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あなたはどうなの？}What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.76,0:02:33.52,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{そ、それはあたしだって自身があるわ。}Well, I am confident all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.52,0:02:34.42,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{でも…}But…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.42,0:02:35.61,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{でもなんなの？}But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.61,0:02:39.93,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{ん、でもさ、「何が何でも絶対に勝つ」なんて、そんな。}But saying that we have to win no matter the costs is a little too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.93,0:02:46.35,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{だって、本郷先生はコーチ降りたのは早川さんが言うように本当に作戦上のことかしら？}But I doubt prof. Hongou left us as a part of his strategy like Hayakawa-san said he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.35,0:02:49.92,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{ね、早川さん、あなたはそう言い切れる自身があって？}Hayakawa-san, do you really believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.79,0:02:52.14,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{ないよね。}You don't, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.14,0:02:53.33,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{ない、ない。}No way. Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.33,0:02:56.92,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{XXX相手は日本の高校チームが構わない、ソ連チームだね。}Our opponent is the Soviet Union that even our high schools can't win with.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.92,0:03:02.54,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{そうよ。いくら自身があっても、毎日本郷先生のコーチがなって、やっぱり少し不安な。}No matter how confident we are, we're a\hlittle worried without professor Hongou.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.16,0:03:04.02,Default,Nakazawa,0,0,0,,{ん。}Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.02,0:03:06.70,Default,Nakazawa,0,0,0,,{今度の全国大会の優勝がいい見本よ。}That All-Japan tournament was a good example.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.70,0:03:08.62,Default,Nakazawa,0,0,0,,{本郷先生はいなきゃ、やっぱりむりよ。}We stand no chance without professor Hongou.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:11.18,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{あたしたちだけじゃ絶対勝てるて言い切らないわ。}We can't say for sure that we will win by ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:12.85,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{いくら自身があっても。ね？}No matter our confidence. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.85,0:03:13.29,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{ね。}Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.29,0:03:14.18,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{行けない。}This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.18,0:03:16.40,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{恐れていた時代成ってしまったわ。}I feared it would come to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:19.12,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{皆、何か勘違いしてるんじゃない？}Girls, aren't you forgetting something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.12,0:03:21.92,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{富士見学園バレー部は日本一なのよ。}Fujimi Academy's volleyball club is the best in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.96,0:03:27.43,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{ソ連が何よ。}So what if they're the Soviet Union?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.43,0:03:32.04,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あたしたちの先輩はソ連に勝てるように、あたしたちだって勝てないわけがないじゃない？}If our seniors can win with them, why can't we do the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.04,0:03:35.39,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{その自身があるかぎり、あたしは絶対に負けないわ。}As long as I believe in myself, I won't lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.39,0:03:38.01,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{いえ、勝てると言う確信があるわ。}Or better put, I will win.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.01,0:03:40.28,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{あたしも勝てると思うわ。}Yep. I think we can win too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.28,0:03:41.41,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—そう？\N—うん。}– Really?\N– Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.12,0:03:44.93,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{この間もテレビのソ連の試合振りを見て思ったの。}I watched the last Soviet Union's game on the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.93,0:03:46.60,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あたしたちは勝てるって。}Because of it, I am sure we can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.60,0:03:50.18,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{いいえ。ソ連を倒すのはわが富士見学園バレー部以外にはないって。}No. There's no way Fujimi Academy can do anything but win with the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.73,0:04:16.98,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{やりましょう、皆。}Let's do this, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:18.57,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—うん。—うん。\N—やろう。}– Yep. – All right.\N– Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.57,0:04:19.89,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—やろうやろう。ね？\N—やるわよ。}– Yeah, yeah.\N– All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.89,0:04:22.43,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—XXX。—皆、頑張れね。—そうよ。}– Let's do our best.\N– Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.43,0:04:24.54,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{さ、千本スパイクよ。位置について。}Let's practice the spike. Assume positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:25.56,Default,(unison),0,0,0,,{—はい！\N—はい！}Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.74,0:04:29.42,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:31.01,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—行くわよ。\N—OK。}– Here I go.\N– OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.01,0:04:32.36,Default,Nakazawa,0,0,0,,{XXX。それ！}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:33.23,Default,Ikezaki,0,0,0,,{はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.23,0:04:34.63,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{ほらほらほら、何やってんだ？}Come on, come on, come on.\NWhatcha doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.63,0:04:35.52,Default,Fukuda,0,0,0,,{それ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.28,0:04:37.29,Default,Ozawa,0,0,0,,{はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.29,0:04:38.79,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{行くわよ。}Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.79,0:04:40.42,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{XXX、いいわよ。}Don't lose your focus!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.42,0:04:40.99,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{それ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.99,0:04:42.22,Default,Ozawa,0,0,0,,{それ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:44.41,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{それ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.41,0:04:44.82,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{あ。}Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.52,0:04:46.28,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{パス。}Pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.97,0:04:50.45,Default,Ozawa,0,0,0,,{だらしないわよ。}Don't be such a klutz.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.45,0:04:51.80,Default,Nakazawa,0,0,0,,{負けるもんか。}I won't lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.80,0:04:54.06,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{ナカ、そんなことじゃソ連に勝てないわよ。}Naka, we won't win with the Soviets like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.38,0:04:58.43,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{そんなことじゃソ連に勝てない？}We won't win with the Soviets like this…?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.43,0:04:59.34,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{もし。}What if?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.34,0:05:01.34,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{いえ、そんなことは絶対にないわ。}No, it can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.04,0:05:04.24,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{でも、万が一ソ連にまけたら…}But what if we lost by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.62,0:05:05.74,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{いいえ。}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.74,0:05:07.16,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{いいえ、でも。}No, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.16,0:05:08.65,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{でも…}But…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.65,0:05:09.52,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あ。}Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.84,0:05:12.92,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{やっぱりソ連に負けたじゃないか？}You lost to the Soviet Union after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.81,0:05:14.63,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{だめだ。}You're hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.63,0:05:19.04,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{勝つ自身があると言ったのは。}– I thought you were confident you'll win?\N{こうなったX新体育館もうじゃね。}– It's a goodbye to the new gym then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.04,0:05:22.74,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{中々XXX優勝XXXこうなるんだ。}You won a single championship and you got this conceited already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.74,0:05:24.78,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{これで無量ほどしたでしょう。}You don't know your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.78,0:05:26.58,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{このさえバレー部なんか解散しろ。}You should just disband the club!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.58,0:05:31.00,Alternative,(mixed),0,0,0,,{XXX！}Disband! Disband!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.00,0:05:32.00,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{止めて。}Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.00,0:05:33.67,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{解散だけは許して。}Anything but disbanding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.67,0:05:35.15,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{お願いよ。}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.15,0:05:36.58,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{解散。}Disband.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.75,0:05:39.95,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{止めて！}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.80,0:05:43.56,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{解散。}Disband.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.97,0:05:45.44,Alternative,(unknown),0,0,0,,{解散。}Disband!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:46.64,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{止めて。}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.96,0:05:52.32,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{どうしたの？}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.32,0:05:54.32,Default,Nakazawa,0,0,0,,{—ね、気分は悪いの？\N—なんでもないわ。}– Are you feeling unwell?\N– It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.32,0:05:56.32,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{さ、皆、張り切ってきましょう。}Come on, girls. Let's get at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.63,0:05:58.42,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{それ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.01,0:05:59.67,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.88,0:06:16.34,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{こずえ。}Kozue.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.34,0:06:20.18,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あなたは本当にソ連に勝てる自身があるの？}Do you really think you can win with the Soviets?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.18,0:06:22.73,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{負ければ皆の前で宣言なんてしないわ。}If I lost, I couldn't face the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.14,0:06:25.39,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{勝つわ。}We'll win.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.39,0:06:27.59,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{ソ連との試合を勝って見せます。}We will show you a victory with the Soviets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.31,0:06:36.06,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{言ってしまった後、あたしはXXXしまったと思った。}I was sure of this back then when I said those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:39.99,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{勝つ自身があっても、試合はやってみなければ分からない。}Even though I believe in us, one can't know the outcome until after the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.99,0:06:42.28,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{でも、もう言ってしまったのよ。}But I went ahead and said that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.07,0:06:44.90,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{そう。}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.90,0:06:47.92,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{もう皆の前ではっきり宣言してしまったの。}I've declared our win in front of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.92,0:06:49.58,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{賽は投げられたのよ。}There's no going back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.58,0:06:53.74,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{それに、あたしの「絶対に勝とう」って言う言葉を信じてくれるメンバー。}Besides, the club members still believe my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.74,0:06:56.90,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{ここまで来たら、何が何でも絶対勝つ以外はないのよ。}At this point there's no option but to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:06:58.90,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{いえ。きっと勝つわ。}We'll win for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.63,0:07:06.80,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{そして努さんXXX、バレーをXXX人たち、皆を見返してやるわ。}We'll triumph over Tsutomu-san and people who've underestimated our club.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:12.90,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{でもそのためにも本郷先生が一番大事な試合の時にコーチおりるなんて卑怯だわ。}But professor Hongou's resignation just before this important game was unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.90,0:07:17.24,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{「何のためにバレーをやるか」なんて聞かれてもすぐ答えられるわけがないわ。}There's no way I could answer on the spot as to why I'm playing volleyball.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:21.43,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{そんなことより目の前にXXX試合に勝つことのほうが大事なのに。}The match that is right in front of our eyes is much more important than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.43,0:07:22.88,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{なのに。}And yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.88,0:07:24.57,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{なのに。}And yet…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.57,0:07:27.23,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{これが先生の例の作戦だったら…}If it only was one of his usual strategic tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.23,0:07:28.28,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あ。}Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.22,0:07:30.77,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{そうでありますように。}If only that was the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.86,0:07:40.00,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{いいえ、行けない。}No, it's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.00,0:07:42.52,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{XXXあたしはそんなに弱気入った行けないわ。}I must stay strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.93,0:07:47.01,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{大事のは勝ってる自身。}A willpower to win is crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.01,0:07:49.38,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{例え本郷先生がいなくても。}With or without professor Hongou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.56,0:07:52.73,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{勝つわ。}We will win.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.73,0:07:53.64,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{勝つわ。}We will win!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.64,0:07:57.01,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)}{日日タイムス}Japan Times
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.82,0:07:59.33,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{それ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.33,0:07:59.93,Default,Kudou,0,0,0,,{はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.18,0:08:00.68,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{ほら。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.35,0:08:02.42,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{XXX。}Don't fall asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.42,0:08:04.76,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{—しっかりしてよ！\N—XXX。}– Keep it together!\N– Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.76,0:08:08.46,Default,Reporter A,0,0,0,,{いよいよソ連との試合が明後日に迫っただけど、どう？自身がある？}The match with the Soviet Union takes place in two days. Do you feel confident?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.46,0:08:09.22,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{はい。}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.22,0:08:11.84,Default,Reporter B,0,0,0,,{え？そう言うことはどう言うことな？}Eh? What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.84,0:08:13.78,Default,Reporter B,0,0,0,,{まさか勝てると言う自身があるわけじゃ。}Surely you don't mean you will win?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.78,0:08:14.78,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{え。そうです。}Precisely, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.78,0:08:16.78,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{勝てると言う自身のことです。}I am confident we will win.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.78,0:08:21.08,Default,Reporter A,0,0,0,,{いくらなんだって君、相手は日本の高校生XXX腕XXXなんだよ。}I'd like to remind you that even the Japanese high schools are no match for your opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.08,0:08:26.00,Default,Reporter B,0,0,0,,{富士見学園は日本一と言っても、ジュニア中が世界一なんだからね。}Even though Fujimi Academy's the best in Japan, they're the best in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.00,0:08:28.93,Default,Reporter C,0,0,0,,{もちろんそれを承知Xで言ってるんでしょうね。}Of course, you're aware of that already, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.93,0:08:29.92,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{もちろんです。}That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.92,0:08:31.94,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{まさか。}You don't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:33.52,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{絶対に勝って見せます。}We'll show you a victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.46,0:08:44.36,Sign,,0,0,0,,{いよいよ明日に迫る日ソ親善ジュニアバレーボール…}The anticipated Japan-Soviet match is tomorrow!
Comment: 0,0:08:44.36,0:08:45.85,Blackboard,,0,0,0,,{日本一の面目にかけてソ連チームに一矢を報いるか！}After wagering their honor, will they win against the Soviet Union?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.70,0:08:45.81,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{見てみろよ。}Check this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:47.81,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{ワ、かっこいい。}Wow, so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.78,0:08:50.38,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{でも本当に勝てるかしら。}But can they really win?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:51.34,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{当たり前さ。}Of course they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.34,0:08:55.48,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{わが効のXXXこずえはとうとう宣言しただもん。勝つに決まってるさ。}Our school's heroine Kozue-san declared it so, so it will be this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.48,0:08:56.99,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{明日の試合が楽しみね。}I'm looking forward to this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.99,0:08:58.99,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{XXXいい席を取ろうよ。}We'd better reserve good seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.99,0:09:00.20,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{あたしのも頼む。}Please get one for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.20,0:09:01.48,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{(XXX・かすれる)まで応援するわ。}I'll cheer her on with all might.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.48,0:09:03.68,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{ソ連チームにXXストレート勝ちだ。}She'll lead our school straight to a victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:04.94,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{ワ。来た来た。}Wah, she's here, she's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.94,0:09:06.64,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—鮎原さん。\N鮎原さん。}– Ayuhara-san!\N– Ayuhara-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.64,0:09:08.78,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—おい、頑張れよ！\N—頑張ってね。}– Do your best!\N– Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.78,0:09:10.31,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{私たちはついてくるよ！}We'll be seeing your game!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.51,0:09:13.22,Default,Mitamura,0,0,0,,{鮎原君。}Ayuhara-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.22,0:09:13.65,Default,Mitamura,0,0,0,,{よ。}Yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.65,0:09:15.01,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あら、三田村さん。おはよう。}Oh, Mitamura-san. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.01,0:09:15.70,Default,Mitamura,0,0,0,,{おはよう。}Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:18.30,Default,Mitamura,0,0,0,,{鮎原君。明日大いに頑張ってくれたまえ。}Ayuhara-kun. Do your best tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.30,0:09:20.27,Default,Mitamura,0,0,0,,{おれ勝利を信じてる。}I believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.27,0:09:21.08,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{ありがとう。}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.08,0:09:22.56,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{ユーフー。}Yoohoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.56,0:09:24.52,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{かっこいい。}So cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.52,0:09:26.03,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{XXX。}You look sweet together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.03,0:09:28.13,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{いいぞ、ロミオとジュリエット。}Good going, Romeo and Juliet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.13,0:09:30.13,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—ハハハハ。\N—羨ましいのよ。}– Hahahaha.\N– I'm so jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:32.13,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—あの、じゃ。\N—じゃ。}– See you around.\N– Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.13,0:09:33.62,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あ、努君。}Ah, Tsutomu-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.79,0:09:45.44,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{励ましの声ぐれかけてくれたって言うのに。}It wouldn't hurt for him to encourage me a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.82,0:09:51.47,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{さ、今日で練習は最後。}Today is the final practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.47,0:09:53.53,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{XXその試合XX紅白試合をしましょう。}We'll hold a practice match.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.53,0:09:56.38,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{相手はソ連中だと思って、皆全力出して打っ付かるのよ。}Our opponent is the Soviet Union. Let's do this properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.38,0:09:57.14,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{いいわね。}Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.14,0:09:58.31,Default,(unison),0,0,0,,{おう。}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.86,0:10:00.75,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{それ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.75,0:10:01.60,Default,Ikezaki,0,0,0,,{はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.30,0:10:03.12,Default,Ooki,0,0,0,,{つれて。}Receive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.02,0:10:04.86,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.86,0:10:05.60,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{それ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:06.24,Default,(unknown),0,0,0,,{いいぞ。}Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.75,0:10:07.65,Default,Ikezaki,0,0,0,,{えい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.65,0:10:08.78,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{あ、本郷先生。}Ah, professor Hongou.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.78,0:10:11.58,Default,(unison),0,0,0,,{—本郷先生！\N—先生！}– Professor Hongou!\N– Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.58,0:10:12.54,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{君たち。}Girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.54,0:10:14.49,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{ソ連チームに勝つと約束したそうだが？}I heard you promised to win with the Soviets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.49,0:10:15.72,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{はい、そうです。}That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.72,0:10:17.41,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{本気でそう思ってるのか？}Do you think you've got what it takes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.41,0:10:18.18,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{え？}Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.97,0:10:26.46,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{今一度聞く。}Let me ask again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:29.86,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{君達は本当にソ連チームに勝てると思っているのか？}Do you really think you can win with the Soviet Union's team?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.02,0:10:33.80,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{思ってます。}I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.80,0:10:34.90,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—思ってます。\N—思ってます。}– We do.\N– We do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.90,0:10:36.46,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{よし、分かった。}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.46,0:10:39.20,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{それじゃ、明日の試合は君たちだけでやってみたまえ。}Well then, I'll be seeing your game tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:40.24,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{え？}Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:42.11,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{そのファイトを忘れずにな。}Don't forget that spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.11,0:10:42.74,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{いいな、皆。}Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.74,0:10:45.12,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{せ-先生、そんな。}P-Professor, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.12,0:10:46.37,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{いいか、鮎原。}Listen, Ayuhara.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.37,0:10:47.98,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{全部君に任せるんだぞ。}I'm leaving everything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.98,0:10:49.64,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{僕は応援席で見ている。}I'll be cheering for you from the seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.25,0:10:59.78,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{なぜそこまで先生はバレー部員、あたしに冷たくするんだろう？}Why is the teacher so cold towards us? Towards me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.84,0:11:03.78,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{卑怯者。}That's unfair!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:05.96,Default,Kashiwagi,0,0,0,,{なにさ、本郷先生なんて。}What is professor Hongou thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.96,0:11:08.13,Default,Fukuda,0,0,0,,{コーチしてくれなくちゃって勝てるんだから。}We can win with or without him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.13,0:11:10.59,Default,Ikezaki,0,0,0,,{その方があたしたちの(X・株が上がれても)のね。}On the contrary, we might do better without him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.59,0:11:11.75,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{—そうよ。\N—そうよ。}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.75,0:11:13.24,Default,Katori,0,0,0,,{さ、練習を続けようよ。}Let's continue the practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.24,0:11:15.24,Default,(unison),0,0,0,,{—おう！\N—おう！}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:16.56,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{よし、やるわ。}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.56,0:11:18.67,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{こうなったら、死んでも勝って見せるわ。}I'll bring us a victory even if it kills me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:34.81,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{本郷君。}Hongou-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.81,0:11:35.40,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{校長。}Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.40,0:11:39.69,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{君。聞くところコーチを休んでるそうだが、どう言うわけかね？}I heard you're no longer coaching the girls. What gives?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.69,0:11:41.76,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{練習だけではありません。}It's not only the practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:44.47,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{明日の試合にもコーチを休むつもりです。}I don't intend to coach them in the tomorrow's game too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.47,0:11:45.75,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{まさか。}As if.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.75,0:11:48.38,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{君、冗談を言ってる場合じゃない。}You know, this is not funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.38,0:11:50.73,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{相手はソ連チームですぞ。ソ連。}The opponent is the Soviet Union. Soviet Union!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.73,0:11:51.34,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{分かってます。}I am aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.34,0:11:53.34,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{いいえ、いいえ、いいえ。分かってはおらん。}No, no, no. Looks like you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.34,0:11:56.63,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{この試合はだな単なる対抗試合じゃないんだ。}This game isn't just some championship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.63,0:12:00.17,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{わが効は日本の代表として、ソ連に挑戦するんじゃ。}It's our chance to challenge the Soviet Union as a Japan's representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.17,0:12:01.13,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{それは分かってます。}I understand this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.13,0:12:03.79,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{そこまで分かっているならなぜ？}If you understand that much, then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.79,0:12:05.72,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{彼女たちのためなんです。}It's for the sake of the girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:06.87,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{な、何だって？}W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.87,0:12:10.14,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{彼女たちはこれからさっきもっと大きく成るために…}In order to let the girls grow bigger from now on…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.14,0:12:14.21,Default,Hongou,0,0,0,,{…私はXXこの大事な試合を棒に振ります。}…I'm willing to sacrifice this match.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.21,0:12:16.62,Default,Principal,0,0,0,,{そ-それじゃ、わが校は負けると…}T-Then, our school will lose…
